quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  6,132,"And for all there are degrees<i class=""s"">(of rank) </i>according to how <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Amer read it as: “…how you acted,”</span>
  6,133,"Thus your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord is the Self-Sufficient, the Possessor of mercy. If He wills, He can do away with you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>and give succession after you to whomever He wills, just as He initiated you from the offspring of other people."
  6,134,"Indeed, what you are promised is coming, and in no way can you thwart<i class=""s"">(God) </i>."
  6,135,"Say, “O my people, act according to <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Shu’ba read it as: “…your positions”</span>
  6,136,"And they set aside for Allah a share of the<i class=""s"">(yield of the) </i>fields and the livestock He created, and they said, “This is for Allah,” according to their claim, “and this is for our associates.” But whatever was<i class=""s"">(deemed) </i>for their associates does not reach Allah, yet whatever was<i class=""s"">(deemed) </i>for Allah reaches their associates. Evil is their judgment!"
  6,137,"Likewise, <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Amer read it as: “Likewise, for many polytheists, the killing of their children has been adorned by their associates in order to…”</span>
